1. *Trupe* su došle na vreme. (The troops arrived on time.)
2. Vojska je bila raspoređena u *trupama*. (The army was deployed in troops.)
3. Nije lako pridružiti se *trupi* kada ne poznaješ nikoga. (It's not easy to join a group when you don't know anyone.)
4. *Trupi* vojnika je bilo naređeno da napadne neprijateljsku bazu. (A troop of soldiers was ordered to attack the enemy base.)
5. Neki *trupi* su krenuli u potragu za nestalim vojnicima. (Some troops set out to search for missing soldiers.)
6. Policija je ispitivala članove *trupe* nakon napada. (The police questioned members of the troupe after the attack.)
7. *Trupe* su marširale kroz grad sa zastavama u rukama. (The troops marched through the city with flags in their hands.)
8. Komandant je dao naređenje *trupama* da se povuku. (The commander ordered the troops to retreat.)

Note: In the Serbian language, the word "trupe" can mean "troops" or "a group of people performing together", which is why it appears in different contexts in the sentences above.